5.3 LoRA Integration Mathematics

Low-Rank Adaptation Formalism:

```
Base network: f(z) = W₂·σ(W₁·z + b₁) + b₂
With LoRA: f_LoRA(z) = (W₂ + B₂A₂)·σ((W₁ + B₁A₁)·z + b₁) + b₂

Where:
A₁ ∈ ℝ^{r×d_in}, B₁ ∈ ℝ^{d_hidden×r}
A₂ ∈ ℝ^{r×d_hidden}, B₂ ∈ ℝ^{d_out×r}
r << min(d_in, d_hidden, d_out)

Gradient computation:
∂f/∂A₁ = B₁ᵀ·(diag(σ')·W₂ᵀ·∂L/∂f)·zᵀ
∂f/∂B₁ = (∂L/∂f)·(W₂·diag(σ'))·A₁·z
(Similarly for A₂, B₂)
```

6. Evaluation Framework

6.1 Quantitative Metrics

Learning Efficiency Metrics:

```
1. Sample Efficiency: η_sample = (R_final - R_initial)/N_samples
2. Convergence Rate: α_conv from fit to R(t) = R_∞ - c·exp(-α·t)
3. Generalization Gap: Δ_gen = |E[R_train] - E[R_test]|
4. Stability Metric: σ_stab = std(R_last_100)/mean(R_last_100)
```

Task-Specific Metrics:

```
Shape Formation:
• Chamfer Distance: CD(S, T) = (1/|S|)Σ_x∈S min_y∈T ||x-y||² + (1/|T|)Σ_y∈T min_x∈S ||x-y||²
• Hausdorff Distance: HD(S, T) = max(sup_x∈S inf_y∈T ||x-y||, sup_y∈T inf_x∈S ||y-x||)
• Skeleton Accuracy: F1 score of extracted medial axis

Navigation:
• Success Rate: % reaching goal
• Path Efficiency: length_optimal/length_actual
• Swarm Coherence: 1 - σ_positions/μ_positions
```

6.2 Statistical Validation Protocol

Multiple Comparison Correction:

```
For M experiments, use Benjamini-Hochberg procedure:
1. Compute p-values for all hypotheses
2. Sort p-values: p_(1) ≤ p_(2) ≤ ... ≤ p_(M)
3. Find largest k such that p_(k) ≤ (k/M)·q
4. Reject hypotheses 1 through k

Where q = 0.05 (false discovery rate)
```

