A. Mathematical Derivations

Backward Pass for SPH with Gradient Stopping:

```
Let ŝ_i = Σ_j (m_j/ρ_j) s_j W_ε(r_ij)
In forward pass: ŝ_i = stop_gradient(ŝ_i)
In backward pass: ∂L/∂s_j = (m_j/ρ_j) W_ε(r_ij) ∂L/∂ŝ_i
But: ∂L/∂ρ_j = 0 (gradient stopped)
```

Entropic Gradient Variance Reduction:

```
Var[∇̂J(θ)] = 𝔼[exp(2βR)(∇logπ)^2]/𝔼[exp(βR)]^2 - 1
Control variate: g_cv = w(τ)(∇logπ - b)
Optimal b = Cov(w∇logπ, w)/Var[w]
```

